==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: July
<hw>Ju*ly"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Julies</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L. <ets>Julius</ets>; --
named from <person>Caius <ets>Julius</ets> Caesar</person>, who was born
in this month: cf. F. <ets>Juillet</ets>.]</ety> <def>The seventh month
of the year, containing thirty-one days.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ This month was called <altname>Quintilis</altname>, or
the fifth month, according to the old Roman calendar, in which March was
the first month of the year.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>July-flower</ent>⟦br⟧
